        </item>
        <item>
            <title>1.8</title>
            <description><![CDATA[
                <ul style="font-size:13px;"><li>New: The control wheel now takes scroll events from the mouse to adjust volume. Place the mouse cursor anywhere over the control wheel and scroll vertically to adjust the volume more fluidly.</li><li>Update: Music Widget more accurately detects when the Music app is launched or terminated.</li><li>Update: Music Widget has enhancements to the Scripting Bridge code for better performance when querying state and info from Music app.</li><li>Fix: This update addresses an issue where playlists wouldn't load if Music app was loaded after Music Widget was launched and displaying  the Playlist chooser.</li><li>Fix: This update addresses an issue where the Preferences window would not restore to its last position on screen.</li><li>Update: Additional information and illustrations for using Music Widget were added to the Help Book.</li></ul>
            ]]></description>
            <pubDate>Thu, 14 Oct 2021 19:20:04 -0700</pubDate>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>11.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <enclosure url="https://marioaguzman.github.io/musicwidget/updater/Music%20Widget.zip" sparkle:version="10" sparkle:shortVersionString="1.8" length="4273774" type="application/octet-stream" sparkle:edSignature="MuXLX/SC4eZ/dkLLFkylMlmrmQAS0iIJy1Lkp3yOWHsKk+YpS5xNSjyfUGxpnxmMNHvdU1Cax7ON7H/NANaYCA=="/>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>1.9</title>
            <description><![CDATA[
                <ul style="font-size:13px;"><li>Built with Xcode 13.1 and the macOS Monterey SDK.</li><li>Update: Using your trackpad to change the volume is now <b>far</b> more precise. Place your cursor over the control wheel and scroll vertically to adjust the volume using your mouse or trackpad.</li></ul>
            ]]></description>
            <pubDate>Sat, 06 Nov 2021 12:41:48 -0700</pubDate>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>11.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
